The paper deals with the problem of source localization using energy samples, which is a common problem in signal processing and communication systems. The use of matrix observation models and matrix factorization techniques suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of cs.SI (Signal Processing), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The development of a robust peak localization algorithm and the focus on decreasing the mean squared error (MSE) suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.SP (Speech Processing) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
